{"comments":"Vibrance — Intelligent saturation adjustment.\n\n## Industry Standard\n\nMirrors AE's Vibrance effect which provides smart saturation:\n\n- **Vibrance**: Increases saturation of muted colors more than\n  already-saturated colors. Protects skin tones from over-saturation.\n\n- **Saturation**: Traditional linear saturation adjustment affecting\n  all colors equally.\n\n## Properties (All Animatable)\n\n| Property | Type | Min | Max | Behavior | Default |\n|----------|------|-----|-----|----------|---------|\n| vibrance | Number | -100.0 | 100.0 | clamps | 0.0 |\n| saturation | Number | -100.0 | 100.0 | clamps | 0.0 |\n\n## Mathematical Model\n\nVibrance uses a non-linear saturation curve:\n- Low-saturation pixels receive more boost\n- High-saturation pixels receive less boost\n- Skin tone hue range (orange-red) is protected\n\nAt vibrance = 100, a 20% saturated pixel might gain 80%,\nwhile an 80% saturated pixel might only gain 20%.\n","declarations":[{"children":[],"comments":"Vibrance effect with smart and linear saturation controls.\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["vibrance",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["saturation",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[104,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Motion/Effects/ColorCorrection/Vibrance.purs","start":[101,1]},"title":"VibranceEffect"},{"children":[],"comments":"Default neutral effect.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Motion","Effects","ColorCorrection","Vibrance"],"VibranceEffect"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[107,40],"name":"../../hydroge